This paper proposes a framework for multi-object tracking, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The paper focuses on using the GMPHD filter and occlusion group management scheme to improve tracking accuracy in the presence of occlusions. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to multimedia (cs.MM) category.
